    <note>Shangguan(1) Ji(2) [15811] He was Hengzhou tuiguan when Zhao(1) Ruyu [3200] was banished to Lingling county and died on the road passing though Hengyang. At this time everbody feared Han(1) Tuozhou [3326] and none dared to manage mourning matters. Ji(2) prepared the corpse for burial by himself. Qian(1) Mou [15812], prefect of Hengzhou and the one who handled the burial, memorialized about the good conduct of Ji(2) and he was promoted. CBD, 1, 29.</note>
